# Default ALSA rate converter for every `plug:` / `plughw:` rate
# conversion on the box. Uses libsamplerate sinc-best from
# libasound2-plugins. Falls back to the built-in "linear" resampler
# if libasound2-plugins isn't installed — which is the failure mode
# that produced ~12 dB of 4-8 kHz loss in shairport's 44.1→48 plug,
# crippling AEC speech-band performance (May 2026 investigation in
# docs/HANDOFF-aec.md). Affects:
#   - shairport-sync writing plughw:Loopback,0,0 (44.1k → 48k)
#   - bluealsa-aplay's plug operations
#   - jasper-aec-bridge reading pcm.jasper_ref (a `plug:` wrapper)
# Pi 5 cost: ~3-5% of one A76 core on the resampler thread. Plenty
# of headroom. Switch to `samplerate_medium` if CPU ever matters.
defaults.pcm.rate_converter "samplerate_best"

# /root/.asoundrc — installed by deploy/install.sh with
# __DONGLE_CARD__ substituted by the detected USB-C dongle name.
#
# Why this file exists:
#   - jasper-voice's TTS needs a path to the speakers that's separate
#     from the CamillaDSP music chain. Without a shared destination,
#     TTS would have to either go through the loopback (mixing with
#     music in unhelpful ways) or directly to the dongle (locked
#     while CamillaDSP holds it).
#   - dmix (`jasper_out`) is that shared destination: CamillaDSP's
#     processed music + jasper-voice's TTS both write here; dmix sums
#     them sample-wise; one stream goes to the dongle.
#
# Topology:
#
#   renderers (librespot, shairport-sync, bluealsa-aplay)
#     → pcm.jasper_renderer_in  (plug wrapping the dmix below)
#                   │
#                   ▼
#         pcm.jasper_renderer_mix  ── dmix ──┐
#                                            │
#                                            ▼
#                  hw:Loopback,0,0  (snd-aloop playback)
#                                            │
#                                            ▼ (loop)
#                  hw:Loopback,1,0  (snd-aloop capture)
#                                            │
#                                            ▼ (plughw, rate-converts)
#                                  jasper-camilla (CamillaDSP)
#                                            │
#                                            ▼ (writes to dmix below)
#                                  pcm.jasper_out  ─── dmix ──┐
#                                                             │
#                  jasper-voice TTS  ─────────────────────────┤  (also writes to dmix)
#                                                             │
#                                                             ▼
#                                                  hw:CARD=__DONGLE_CARD__,DEV=0
#                                                       Apple USB-C dongle → speakers
#
# Why the renderer-side dmix (added 2026-05-22): snd-aloop's
# `hw:Loopback,0,0` is single-writer. Before this layer existed, any
# attempt by a second renderer to open the loopback while another
# held it returned ALSA -EBUSY (16). The user-visible symptoms:
#   - librespot crash-looped 3-5× on EBUSY when shairport had the
#     loopback open during a phantom AirPlay SETUP (45 s of stall).
#   - "latest source wins" handover from AirPlay → Spotify Connect
#     silently failed because librespot couldn't take the device.
# Inserting a dmix in front lets all three renderers hold the FD
# simultaneously; the dmix sums their streams sample-wise and writes
# one stream to snd-aloop. Mux's job (latest-source-wins) shifts from
# implicit-via-EBUSY to explicit-via-MPRIS/Web-API pauses — see
# jasper.mux for the contract. dmix's own format/rate is fixed
# (48 kHz S16_LE 2ch); renderers reach it through `pcm.jasper_renderer_in`
# (a `plug:` wrapper) so each can write its native format / rate and
# `samplerate_best` (set at the top of this file) handles conversion.
#
# When the AEC bridge is enabled (see CLAUDE.md "Acoustic echo
# cancellation"), the `pcm.jasper_capture` dsnoop tap below lets
# CamillaDSP and the AEC bridge share the loopback capture side as
# multiple readers. dsnoop is the multi-reader-safe ALSA primitive
# (the dual of dmix on the playback side). The dsnoop slave is
# configured for 48 kHz S16_LE stereo — the rate the bridge and
# CamillaDSP both target internally.
#
# RATE LOCK (former footgun, now neutralised by jasper_renderer_mix):
# snd-aloop's parameters are set by whichever process opens
# hw:Loopback,0,0 first (Matrix:Module-aloop on the ALSA wiki). Before
# 2026-05-22, that was whichever renderer started first — typically
# shairport at 44.1 kHz, which locked the loopback to 44.1 until
# every consumer closed it. After 2026-05-22 the renderer-side dmix
# opens the loopback at its declared rate (48 kHz S16_LE) and holds
# it open for the lifetime of any renderer process; the rate is now
# fully deterministic and downstream consumers can rely on 48 kHz.
#
# Two readers, two access paths:
#   - CamillaDSP opens `plug:jasper_capture` (note the `plug:`) in
#     v1.yml. plug auto-converts rate/format, so camilla is rate-
#     tolerant: works whether the loopback is 44.1 or 48.
#   - AEC bridge opens `jasper_ref` (defined below) — a plug-wrapped
#     alias of jasper_capture. Mirrors the same pattern. The bridge
#     gets samples at whatever rate it requests via alsaaudio,
#     regardless of the loopback's actual locked rate.
#
# Why two names: keeps `pcm.jasper_capture` semantically "the raw
# dsnoop tap" so other consumers / diagnostics see exactly what
# the kernel produced, while `pcm.jasper_ref` advertises its
# intent ("AEC reference, rate-agnostic") at the call site.
#
# We never want camilla to read `hw:Loopback,1,0` directly — that
# would deny dsnoop the slave, and the bridge would fail to open
# with `unable to open slave`.

# Renderer-side dmix: all three renderers (librespot, shairport-sync,
# bluealsa-aplay) write here instead of opening hw:Loopback,0,0
# directly. Multi-writer-safe; sums sample-wise; writes one stream to
# snd-aloop. See the comment block at the top of this file for the
# why-this-exists rationale. Parameters mirror jasper_out (the dongle
# dmix) for consistency: 48 kHz S16_LE stereo, period 1024 / buffer
# 4096. ipc_key 7779 (unique vs 7777=jasper_out, 7778=jasper_capture).
pcm.jasper_renderer_mix {
    type dmix
    ipc_key 7779
    ipc_perm 0666
    slave {
        pcm "hw:Loopback,0,0"
        rate 48000
        channels 2
        format S16_LE
        period_size 1024
        buffer_size 4096
    }
    bindings {
        0 0
        1 1
    }
}

# Plug-wrapped front-end for renderers. Each renderer references
# `jasper_renderer_in` in its service unit / config file; plug
# handles rate + format conversion from the renderer's native shape
# (e.g. librespot S24_3 44.1 kHz, shairport-sync S32 44.1 kHz,
# bluez-alsa S16 48 kHz) down to the dmix's fixed 48 kHz S16_LE.
# Resampling quality is governed by `defaults.pcm.rate_converter`
# at the top of this file (samplerate_best — same libsamplerate
# library that the rest of the chain uses, ~3-5% of one Pi 5 core
# per active resampling renderer).
pcm.jasper_renderer_in {
    type plug
    slave.pcm "jasper_renderer_mix"
}

pcm.jasper_capture {
    type dsnoop
    ipc_key 7778
    ipc_perm 0666
    slave {
        pcm "hw:Loopback,1,0"
        rate 48000
        channels 2
        format S16_LE
        period_size 1024
        buffer_size 4096
    }
    bindings {
        0 0
        1 1
    }
}

# Plug-wrapped alias for the AEC bridge's reference capture.
#
# `plug` transparently resamples whatever the dsnoop delivers to
# whatever the bridge opens with. The bridge opens at 48 kHz S16_LE
# (per REF_RATE in jasper/cli/aec_bridge.py); plug converts from
# the dsnoop's actual delivered rate (typically 44.1 kHz today due
# to shairport native, sometimes 48 kHz with Spotify Connect) to
# the requested 48 kHz. CPU cost is sub-1% of a Pi 5 core at S16
# stereo / speech rates; latency cost is a few ms of buffer.
#
# Without this wrapper, the bridge would receive distorted or
# silent samples when the loopback's locked rate ≠ 48 kHz —
# the root cause of the AEC-broken-with-AirPlay regression
# diagnosed on 2026-05-15.
pcm.jasper_ref {
    type plug
    slave.pcm "jasper_capture"
}

ctl.jasper_capture {
    type hw
    card Loopback
}

pcm.jasper_out {
    type dmix
    ipc_key 7777
    ipc_perm 0666
    slave {
        pcm "hw:CARD=__DONGLE_CARD__,DEV=0"
        rate 48000
        channels 2
        format S16_LE
        period_size 1024
        buffer_size 4096
    }
    bindings {
        0 0
        1 1
    }
}

ctl.jasper_out {
    type hw
    card __DONGLE_CARD__
}
